(9304, '237600000X', 'Speech, Language and Hearing Service Providers', 'Audiologist-Hearing Aid Fitter', NULL, 'An audiologist/hearing aid fitter is the professional who specializes in evaluating and treating people with hearing loss, conducts a wide variety of tests to determine the exact nature of an individual\'s hearing problem, presents a variety of treatment options to patients, dispenses and fits hearing aids, administers tests of balance to evaluate dizziness and provides hearing rehabilitation training. This classification should be used where individuals are licensed as \"audiologist-hearing aid fitters\" as opposed to states that license individuals as \"audiologists\".', '2002-04-01', '2024-11-15 15:13:16', '2024-11-15 15:13:16'),
(9305, '237700000X', 'Speech, Language and Hearing Service Providers', 'Hearing Instrument Specialist', NULL, 'Individuals who test hearing for the selection, adaptation, fitting, adjusting, servicing, and sale of hearing aids. Hearing Instrument Specialist is a designation provided individuals who qualify by the National Hearing Aid Society', '2002-04-01', '2024-11-15 15:13:16', '2024-11-15 15:13:16'),
